lemcVE.reading2.text="[note] Open your mouth with the word of God, and judge all things fairly: In Hebrew this verse is very different and its second half contains a well known problem of translation. [note] Winding off wool and flax, she makes: The majority of verbs in what follows are aorist, but this is simply because the Hebrew employs the ’perfect’. [note] The ways of her household are careful: Literally ’watertight’."

